text: Magnus Petersson (born 17 June 1975 in Gothenburg) is a Swedish archer. Petersson competed at the 1996 Summer Olympics, the 2000 Summer Olympics, the 2004 Summer Olympics, and the 2008 Summer Olympics.Magnus PeterssonMagnus PETERSSON ==References== Category:1975 births Category:Living people Category:Swedish archers Category:Olympic silver medalists for Sweden Category:Sportspeople from Gothenburg
